            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Same issue here I believe, output from Sonnet:\n\nThe snap package itself (v0.12.0-dev-1812, a dev build) has an internal\n  mismatch. There are two different vim.so parsers bundled at different paths (different\n  MD5 checksums), and the highlights.scm query file references a \"substitute\" node type\n  that at least one of those parsers doesn't support.\n\n   /snap/nvim/4621/usr/lib/.../parser/vim.so  ← b3108...\n   /snap/nvim/4621/usr/share/.../parser/vim.so ← c05cd...  ← mismatched!",
